%T A393448 1136,1261,1392,1530,1674,1825,1982,2146,2316,2493,2676,2866,3062,
%U A393448 3265,3474,3690,3912,4141,4376,4618,4866,5121,5382,5650,5924,6205,6492,6786,7086,7393,7706,8026,8352,8685,9024,9370,9722,10081,10446,10818
%N A393448 a(n) = 3*n^2-2*n+1+floor(n^2/4).
%C A393448 a(n) is the maximum number of regions that can be formed in the plane by drawing n Wynn (rune) shapes of any size and orientation.
%D A393448 David O. H. Cutler, Jonas Karlsson, and Neil J. A. Sloane, Cutting a Pancake with an Exotic Knife, In preparation, March 25 2026.
%H A393448 Jonas Karllson, <a href="/A393448/a393448.jpg">A single Wynn, illustrating a(1) = 2</a>
%H A393448 Jonas Karlsson, <a href="/A393448/a393448_1.jpg">Illustration for a(2) = 10</a>
%H A393448 N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="/A393448/a393448_3.jpg">A hand-drawn Wynn</a>
%F A393448 G.f: (1+6*x^2+6*x^3)/((1+x)*(1-x)^3).
%F A393448 a(n) = 3*a(n-1) - 3*a(n-2) + a(n-3) + 1 for n >= 4.
%Y A393448 This is one of over 25 sequences mentioned in the C-K-S paper.
%Y A393448 Cf. A386486.
%K A393448 nonn,new
